Month = {OCT},
Abstract = {Daubenya Lindl. was until recently thought to comprise the single
   species D. aurea Lindl. but is now considered to include the monotypic
   genera Androsiphon Schltr. and Amphisiphon W.F.Barker, as well as the
   species previously referred to the genus Neobakeria Schltr. Eight
   species are now recognized in the genus, including the new combinations
   Daubenya comata (Burch. ex Baker) J.C. Manning \& A.M.van der Merwe and
   D. zeyheri (Kunth) J.C. Manning \& A.M. van der Merwe. Each species is
   fully described and illustrated in black-and-white and in colour. A key
   to the species, and distribution maps are provided.},
