   AND CROSS-AMPLIFICATION IN OTHER CONGENERIC SPECIES},
Journal = {AMERICAN JOURNAL OF BOTANY},
Year = {2010},
Volume = {97},
Number = {3},
Pages = {E10-E13},
Month = {MAR},
Abstract = {Premise of the study: Microsatellite loci from a genomic library of the
   species Narcissus papyraceus were optimized and characterized for
   studies of population genetics.
   Methods and Results: Eleven markers that were successfully amplified
   showed polymorphism when tested on 50 individuals from two populations
   in southern Spain and northern Morocco. Overall, the number of alleles
   per locus ranged between 4 and 15. Between 8 and 11 loci successfully
   amplified in other eight Narcissus species.
   Conclusions: These markers will enable genetic diversity studies of N.
   papyraceus across its distribution range and conduct paternity analyses
   among individuals differing in flower morphology.},
